quran[38]{c,v,t}:
  56,1,When there happeneth Event
  56,2,There is about its happening no lie
  56,3,Abasing exalting
  56,4,"This will happen when the earth is shaken, shaken"
  56,5,"And the mountains are crumbled, crumbled"
  56,6,So that they become dust seattered
  56,7,And ye are classes three
  56,8,Those on the right hand; how happy shall those on the right hand be
  56,9,And those on the left hand; how miserable shall those on the left hand be
  56,10,And the preceders are the pre-ceders
  56,11,Those! they shall be the brought nigh
  56,12,In Gardens of Delight
  56,13,A multitude from the ancients
  56,14,And a few from the later generations
  56,15,On couches in wrought with gold
  56,16,Reclining thereon facing each other
  56,17,There shall go round Unto them youths ever-young
  56,18,With goblets and ewers and a cup of limpid drink
  56,19,Whereby there shall be neither headiness nor will they be inebriated
  56,20,And with fruit from that which they choose
  56,21,And with flesh of fowls from that Which they desire
  56,22,And there will be fair ones large eyed
  56,23,The likes Unto pearls hidden
  56,24,A recompense for that which they have been working
  56,25,Therein they hear no vain or sinful discourse
  56,26,"Nought but the saying: peace! peace"
  56,27,And the fellows on the right hand; how be happy shall the fellows on the right hand be
  56,28,Midst lote-trees thornless
  56,29,And plantains laden with fruit
  56,30,And a shade ever-spread
  56,31,And water everflowing
  56,32,And fruit abundant
  56,33,Neither ending nor forbidden
  56,34,And carpets raised
  56,35,Verily We! We have created those maidens by a creation
  56,36,And have made them virgins
  56,37,"Loving, of equal age"
  56,38,For the fellows on the right hand